# Diff-Only Editing Rules

- NEVER overwrite a file entirely.
- ALWAYS use string replacement or partial edits (diff) to apply changes.
- If a change requires modifying more than 30 lines, YOU MUST first propose a plan to break it down into smaller, logical steps.
- Preserve existing indentation and coding style exactly.
- Do not add comments or change code that is not directly related to the task.
